"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850933","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Department is working with the defence sector through the Defence Growth Partnership to enable growth across the defence sector with a focus on productivity and competitiveness. Government will consider any sector deal proposal from the defence sector alongside other prospective sector deals as those proposals mature.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-05T14:51:03.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850933/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850933/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850933/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-27","Defence: Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans the Government has to seek a Defence Sector Deal.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","130143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850934","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 22 February 2018 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-02-19/128062/" target="_blank">128062</a>.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-03-06T13:54:06.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850934/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850934/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850934/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-27","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding the Government plans to provide to support care providers in funding the (a) historical capital costs and (b) ongoing revenue costs of complying with the recent tribunal ruling on sleep-in payments and the national minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","130144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850935","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-05","<p>BEIS officials are in regular contact with BAE Systems who are keeping us informed of developments and progress with their redundancy programme. This recent redundancy announcement is a commercial decision by the company. I appreciate that this is a worrying time for BAE Systems’ employees and their families and the Department is working with the Ministry of Defence and the Department for Work and Pensions in discussing potential options to support those affected workers. BAE Systems are also working with Government via the Defence Growth Partnership to consider plans for future growth opportunities across the sector.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-03-05T14:51:30.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850935/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850935/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850935/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-27","BAE Systems: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent discussions officials of his Department have had with BAE Systems on that company's ongoing redundancy programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","130145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850936","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-05","<p>All existing SMI claimants will be offered a loan. Claimants are given information about how the SMI loan will work, about alternatives to the loan and organisations that may offer further information and support. This is followed up by telephone calls to explain the information and answer any questions. A leaflet containing Frequently Asked Questions is issued to support this informed discussion. Where a claimant expresses an interest in taking up the offer of an SMI loan they will be sent a loan agreement and charge form to complete and return. They also receive detailed guidance on how to complete these documents.</p><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-05T17:52:10.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850936/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850936/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850936/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answers of 8 January 2018 to Questions 121064, 121066 and 121067, what information his Department has provided to people claiming welfare support to confirm that they are eligible for a loan.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","130146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850937","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-05","<p>We engage at a personal and individual level with all of our claimants and are committed to tailoring the support that we give and any conditionality requirements to the specific circumstances of the individuals, such as disabilities and mental health conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Sanctions are only ever used as a last resort when claimants have failed to meet their conditionality requirements without good reason. When considering whether a sanction is appropriate, a Decision Maker will take all the claimant’s individual circumstances, including any health conditions or disabilities, and any evidence of good cause, into account before deciding whether a sanction is warranted.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-05T15:05:18.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850937/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850937/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850937/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many sanctions have been imposed on universal credit claimants who are (a) disabled and (b) experiencing mental health problems in the most recent 12 months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","130147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850939","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-05","<p>General practitioners (GPs) are independent contractors who hold contracts with NHS England to provide primary medical services for the National Health Service. Under the terms of their contract, GPs are required to provide certain medical reports or complete certain forms, such as those required to support a claim for incapacity benefit, free of charge to their registered patients.</p><p> </p><p>Outside of contractual requirements, GPs also provide a variety of other services which successive Governments have regarded as private matters between the patient and the GP providing these services. In such cases, decisions on whether to charge a fee and the level of the fee charged are at the GP’s discretion. Where GPs intend to charge for services to patients, the British Medical Association (BMA) advises them to forewarn patients, at the earliest opportunity, of the likely level of fees. The BMA also produces guidance on the level of fees that should be charged for various services.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-05T15:51:57.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850939/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850939/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850939/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-27","General Practitioners: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what guidance his Department has issued to general practitioners on charging to provide medical evidence to support benefit claims.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850940","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-05","<p>Wave 2 of the Challenge Fund closed to applications on 26th January 2018. We expect to notify applicants about the successful applications in March 2018 and we anticipate that the next wave of the Challenge Fund will open to applications in the summer of 2018.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-05T10:51:44.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850940/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850940/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850940/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-27","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, on what date he expects Wave 3 of the Local Full Fibre Network Challenge Fund to open for applications.","false","Biography information for Martin Whitfield","East Lothian","Martin Whitfield","130149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850941","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-05","<p>The information requested is not recorded centrally and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-05T15:05:32.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850941/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850941/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850941/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Universal Credit easements from conditionality have been applied to (a) claimants experiencing a period of sickness, (b) claimants suffering a bereavement following the death of a partner, child or qualifying young person, (c) claimants receiving treatment for drug and alcohol dependency and (d) claimants who are main carers of a Child in Considerable Distress.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","130150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850942","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-06","<p>The Department has not carried out an evaluation in this area. For claimants with a physical or mental impairment (including those with cognitive or learning difficulties) work coaches may agree to tailor the number of hours, type and location of work depending on the claimants’ impairment. In addition, work search and availability requirements must be lifted for certain periods of time to account for a period of sickness. Outside of these set periods, work coaches have the discretion to tailor requirements depending on what is reasonable based on the claimant’s health condition.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-06T11:16:55.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850942/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850942/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850942/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Universal Credit: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department has conducted an evaluation into Work Coaches' tailoring of the Universal Credit Claimant Commitment for people with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","130151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850943","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-05","<p>General Practitioners (GPs) are already directly reimbursed for providing medical evidence to DWP for Attendance Allowance, Disability Living Allowance and Personal Independence Payment claims and when the claimant is potentially terminally ill for benefits which have special provisions for terminally ill people. GPs are also contractually obliged through their contract with NHS England to provide medical evidence for Employment and Support Allowance claims.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-05T16:28:14.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850943/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850943/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850943/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether she has assessed the potential merits of reimbursing general practitioners for providing medical evidence to support benefit claims; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850945","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-07","<p>DWP reviewed and updated its national guidance to staff on managing customer declarations of intention to attempt suicide or self-harm in November 2016. This was part of a programme of regular reviews we undertake to ensure guidance is meeting the need for staff and customers. The guidance requires jobcentres to hold local plans that identify the approach to take, local contacts and support and to review and revise these local plans regularly to ensure information is accurate and appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>A further regular review is currently taking place to ensure our policies and guidance remain current. Any changes identified as a result will be applied to guidance later this year.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-07T17:26:05.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850945/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850945/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850945/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Jobcentre Plus: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when her Department most recently revised its guidance to jobcentre staff on managing customer declarations of intention to attempt suicide or self-harm.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","130153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850946","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-05","<p>The estimated cost of the Royal Free and North London Breast Screening Service for 2018-19 is not currently available centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust advises that it plans to employ 26.45 (whole time equivalent) mammographers on the North London Breast Screening Service for 2018/19.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","130157","2018-03-05T15:50:47.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850946/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850946/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850946/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-27","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the estimated cost is of the Royal Free and North London Breast Screening Service for 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850947","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-05","<p>Jobcentre work coaches are required to set reasonable requirements of customers, review compliance, identify cases of non-compliance and make referrals to a Decision Maker for consideration of if a sanction is appropriate in particular circumstances. Throughout this process, work coaches and decision makers take into account individual customer circumstances, including any vulnerability, complex need or health issue.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance for Employment and Support Allowance, Income Support and Universal Credit cases, covers the requirement for a home visit to be undertaken before making a referral to a Decision Maker for whether or not to consider a sanction, where someone has a condition that could affect their ability to understand and comply with a specific requirement.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-03-05T15:06:10.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850947/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850947/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850947/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-27","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether jobcentre staff are required to undertake a safeguarding visit before imposing a sanction on a vulnerable customer.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","130155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850949","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-05","<p>​We are closely following developments in Afrin in north-western Syria, and the Foreign Secretary and other Ministers are in regular contact with their Turkish counterparts. We have called for de-escalation and the protection of civilians. While recognising Turkey's legitimate interest in the security of its borders, it remains in our shared interest to focus on achieving a political settlement that ends the war and suffering, provides stability for all Syrians and the wider region, and secures the enduring defeat of Daesh.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-05T17:36:55.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850949/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850949/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850949/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-27","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Government of Turkey on military operations against the Democratic Federation of Northern Syria.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","130156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850950","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-05","<p>The estimated cost of the Royal Free and North London Breast Screening Service for 2018-19 is not currently available centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust advises that it plans to employ 26.45 (whole time equivalent) mammographers on the North London Breast Screening Service for 2018/19.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","130154","2018-03-05T15:50:47.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850950/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850950/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850950/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-27","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many mammographers are planned for employment under the Royal Free and North London Breast Screening Service in 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","130157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850951","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-05","<p>Diplomatically, the UK does not support any unilateral declaration of autonomy or independence in Syria – Syria's constitutional arrangements must be decided through the UN-led Geneva process. In that context, we will continue to support a political settlement which provides protection for the rights of all Syrians including the Kurds. Militarily, we will continue to play an active role in the Global Coalition against Daesh which has supported the Syrian Democratic Forces in pushing Daesh out of territory in north-east Syria. We will continue to provide humanitarian aid to help meet the needs of the population in north-east Syria.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-05T17:45:33.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850951/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850951/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850951/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-27","Syria: Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 17 January 2018 to Question HL4467 on Syria: Kurds, whether the Government plans to provide (a) diplomatic, (b) military, and (c) humanitarian support to the Democratic Federation of Northern Syria.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","130158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850952","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-05","<p>Ofcom publishes quarterly data on the volume of consumer complaints that it has received against the major providers of telecoms and pay TV services. This, together with Ofcom’s new Comparing Service Quality report, allows consumers to compare companies performance against a variety of different metrics, enabling them to make informed decisions. In addition, in the Digital Economy Act 2017, the government strengthened Ofcom’s powers to require telecoms companies to provide them with information, including on complaints.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-05T10:55:05.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850952/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850952/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850952/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-27","Telecommunications: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the (a) detail and (b) quality of Ofcom’s quarterly telecoms complaints data on the ability of consumers to make informed decisions.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","130159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850954","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-05","<p>Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR) schemes in the telecoms sector already publish quarterly data about complaints they receive from each communications provider. Ombudsman Services complaints data can be viewed at : https://www.ombudsman-services.org/for-consumers/complaints-data/communications-complaints-data-2017. Communications &amp; Internet Services Adjudication Scheme (CISAS) complaint data can be viewed at : https://www.cedr.com/cisas/quarterly-case-data/. In addition, Ofcom’s 2017 Comparing Service Quality publication includes a section about ADR complaints (page 61) that can be viewed at: https://www.ofcom.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0012/100605/comparing-service-quality-report.pdf. This information enables consumers to make better informed decisions.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-05T10:53:14.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850954/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850954/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850954/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-27","Telecommunications: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of including data from Alternative Dispute Resolution schemes in Ofcom’s quarterly telecoms complaints data to enable consumers to make better informed decisions.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","130160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850955","Department for Education","false","2018-03-07","<p>The department’s work in scoping a review of the outcomes of and support for Children in Need consulted a range of organisations and individuals, including from: sector representatives, children’s charities, local children’s services departments, primary and secondary schools, research organisations and related cross-government teams. This involved speaking to over 120 individuals, including more than 25 social workers, around 40 social worker leaders and around 40 school leaders. This engagement took the form of individual meetings, roundtables, participation in cross-government events and deep dive visits to local services in Birmingham, Solihull and Blackpool, as areas with different profiles of need.</p><p>In addition to the evidence provided by this direct consultation, the department considered emerging learning from projects funded through the Children’s Social Care Innovation Programme, reviewed academic literature, and assessed data collected through the annual Children in Need census.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-07T16:20:21.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850955/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850955/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850955/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-27","Children: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February to Question 125796, on vulnerable children, which professionals, schools and other experts have been consulted as part of the Government's scoping exercise; and what evidence has assessed during that work.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","130161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850956","Home Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>Child sexual exploitation is abhorrent and the crimes perpetrated in Newcastle have had a devastating impact on the lives of the victims. The Government acknowledges the seriousness of the issues raised in this serious case review and is committed to improving the national response to tackling sexual exploitation.</p><p>We have already taken significant action to tackle this issue. In February 2017, the Government published its Tackling Child Sexual Exploitation: Progress Report and announced a £40m package of measures to protect children and young people from sexual abuse, exploitation and trafficking, and to crack down on offenders.</p><p>This included £7.5m for a new, ground-breaking Centre of Expertise that will identify, generate, and share high quality evidence of what works to prevent and tackle child sexual abuse and exploitation. The recommendations of the review cover a wide range of issues, which we will consider carefully in the context of this existing programme of work.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-07T18:16:44.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850956/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850956/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850956/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-27","Sexual Offences: Newcastle upon Tyne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the Government plans to respond to the joint serious case review into sexual exploitation in Newcastle.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","130162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850957","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-05","<p>During October 2017 there were around 6,440 Regular Army applications. Application data for November 2017 onwards is not currently available.</p><p>Between 1 October and 31 December 2017, there were 1,700 Regular Army enlistments.</p><p>The application and enlistment data is not directly comparable. Many of those applied since October will still be in the recruitment process.</p><p>All figures should be considered provisional and subject to review.</p><p><strong>Notes/Caveats:</strong></p><p>The figures include soldiers, untrained officers and officer cadets.</p><p>Enlistment data excludes trained direct entrants into Phase 2 training, those who rejoin and others who enter directly into the trained strength.</p><p>Application data is a single service estimate.</p><p>Figures have been rounded to 10; numbers ending in &quot;5&quot; have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-05T17:52:55.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850957/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850957/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850957/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-27","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 5 February 2018 to Question 125923 on Army: Recruitment, how many people (a) applied and (b) enlisted in the regular army in October to December 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","130163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850958","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-06","<p>All schemes delivered though Highways England’s Cycling, Safety and Integration designated fund must demonstrate value for money using an appraisal developed with key stakeholders. This assesses a number of potential benefits such as increased trips and accidents savings. Highways England continues to develop its evaluation process for different designated funds, starting with the Cycling, Safety and Integration designated fund, in order to measure the effectiveness of the projects delivered and ensure that future programmes maximise their benefits.</p><p> </p><p>The total budget for the Cycling, Safety and Integration designated fund is £175m until 2020. Of that sum £53.5m had been spent by January 2018 which represents 31% of the total. The Cycling, Safety and Integration designated fund spend for the 2016/17 financial year was £18.1m.</p><p> </p><p>The expectation has been that Highways England would develop schemes for this fund in the early years of the first road investment period, and then build them in the later years. The effect of this should be that that more schemes are built in the next two years than in the past two.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-03-06T15:55:32.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850958/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850958/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850958/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-27","Cycling: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Highways England designated fund for cycling, safety and integration; and how much of that fund was spent in 2016/17.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","130164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850960","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-07","<p>We are working with a number of other countries to explore the best ways to develop our current trade and investment relationships and ensure that Britain becomes a global leader in free trade once we leave the EU. Automotive is an important sector for the UK and a trade success story with exports worth £40bn – 13.3% of the UK’s total manufacturing exports. It is crucially important to understand the priorities for the sector, as we develop a future UK trade policy and the Department for International Trade officials maintain a dialogue with the industry, working closely with officials in the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, the Department for Exiting the European Union and other government departments.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-03-07T14:59:00.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850960/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850960/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850960/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-02-27","Trade Agreements: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which non-EU countries his Department has identified as best for future trade deals in the automotive sector.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","130165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850961","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-05","<p>On 13 February 2018, the Secretary of State announced his decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore. The position on funding for this scheme is as set out in the Secretary of State’s decision letter of 13 February 2018 which is available on the GOV.UK website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/network-rail-hope-valley-capacity-order" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/network-rail-hope-valley-capacity-order</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-05T09:01:59.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850961/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850961/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850961/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-27","Manchester-Sheffield Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport,  whether his Department has allocated funding for Network Rail's Hope Valley Capacity Order.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","130166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850962","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-06","<p>On 13 February 2018, the Secretary of State announced his decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore. Network Rail have completed the single option design for the railway infrastructure scheme proposed in the Hope Valley and the timetable for further work on this scheme will be announced in due course.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-06T15:45:23.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850962/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850962/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850962/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-27","Manchester-Sheffield Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when construction work is planned to start on Network Rail's Hope Valley Capacity Order.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","130167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850963","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-05","<p>The Department’s value for money assessment includes assumptions about the financial merits of increasing the number of passenger services on this route. This assessment will need to be refreshed as part of taking forward further work on this scheme. Decisions about future franchise changes will be assessed on their merits as part of this further work.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-03-05T09:04:41.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850963/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850963/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850963/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-27","Manchester-Sheffield Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for train operating companies to operate increased services on Network Rail's Hope Valley Capacity Order.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","130168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850965","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-07","​The Foreign Secretary discussed this issue with his counterpart, the Polish Minister of Foreign Affairs, on 15 February 2018.","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-03-07T15:22:49.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850965/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850965/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850965/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-27","Poland: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to his counterpart in the Government of Poland on their Holocaust law.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","130169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850966","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-05","<p>Central government does not collate this information.</p><p>Local government workforce matters are devolved and it is for councils as independent employers to make decisions on staff disciplinary. This information will be held locally.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-03-05T09:07:07.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850966/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850966/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-27","Local Government: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many local government employees were suspended on full pay in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","130170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850967","Home Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>It has been the policy of successive Governments neither to confirm nor deny matters relating to the activities of the security and intelligence services.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-03-07T15:00:24.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850967/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850967/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850967/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-27","Intelligence Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Deptartment, what the Government's policy is on the destruction of security service files on the political activities of private individuals.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","130171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850968","Department for Transport","false","2018-03-06","<p>The Department issued guidance “Using a phone or a sat nav when driving” which is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/using-mobile-phones-when-driving-the-law" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/using-mobile-phones-when-driving-the-law</a></p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-03-06T15:51:46.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850968/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850968/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-27","Driver Information Systems: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, What guidance his Department has been issued on drivers using satellite navigational apps on mobile phones whilst driving vehicles.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","130172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850970","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-05","<p>HMRC has not prosecuted any companies under the Money Laundering, Terrorist Financing and Transfer of Funds (Information on the Payer) Regulations 2017 in the last eight months since its enactment.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC successfully prosecuted one individual under the Money Laundering Regulations 2007 in 2016/17 and one individual in 2017/18 to date.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-05T16:44:16.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850970/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850970/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-27","Money Laundering: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies have been prosecuted by HMRC under the Money Laundering Regulations 2017 in the last year.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","130173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850971","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-05","<p>This is an operational matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), who are independent from Government. The question has been passed on to the FCA. The FCA will reply directly to the honourable member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-03-05T15:54:09.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850971/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850971/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850971/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-27","Money Laundering: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies have been prosecuted under the Money Laundering Regulations 2017 by the Financial Conduct Authority in the past 12 months.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","130174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850972","Home Office","false","2018-05-03","<p>This Government is committed to the Prevent programme: Prevent's spend was £37.7 million in 2016-17, and is allocated £45.5 million from 2017-18. Prevent is working and is successful. Prevent has made a significant impact in safeguarding people being drawn into terrorism.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","130176","2018-05-03T16:18:30.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850972/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850972/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850972/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-27","Counter-terrorism: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much funding was allocated to the Prevent strand of the counter-terrorism strategy in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","130175"
