"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850107","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-01","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not collect data on traders that have not registered for VAT. They have not registered with HMRC and do not submit VAT returns.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-01T17:21:03.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850107/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850107/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-26","Small Businesses: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many small traders received an exemption from value added tax below the turnover limit for VAT registration in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850108","Department for Education","false","2018-03-06","<p>Teacher numbers are at an all-time high; there are over 457,000 FTE teachers in state-funded schools throughout England. There are 15,500 secondary phase religious education (RE) teachers, and this number has remained broadly stable since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>We recruited 405 trainee RE teachers in 2017/18. To recruit even more RE teachers, we are continuing to offer a generous bursary of up to £9,000 for RE trainee teachers. There are also School Direct salaried places for RE trainees, where trainees can receive a salary during their training year.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-03-06T17:50:16.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850108/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850108/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-26","Religion: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to ensure there is an adequate number of religious education teachers.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","129676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850109","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-06","<p>There are five registered VAT numbers who make regular claims under this scheme.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-03-06T15:59:15.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850109/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850109/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-26","Public Bodies: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many Northern Ireland Government bodies received refunds of VAT incurred on non-business purchases under the section 99 refund scheme in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","129677"
