"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850137","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-06","<p>NHS Improvement has informed the Department that they ask foundation trusts, to report how many subsidiaries have been consolidated into their accounts. In returns received by NHS Improvement for the year ended 31 March 2017, foundation trusts reported 41 consolidated subsidiaries (excluding any consolidated National Health Service charitable funds).</p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of NHS trusts that have set up or are in the process of setting up subsidiary companies is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>NHS trusts do not have an express statutory power to form or participate in ownership of a company other than for income generation purposes. NHS organisations have a duty to operate efficiently and economically and are responsible for putting in place the most effective structures they need to deliver services to their patients within available resources.</p><p> </p><p>Both the Department and NHS Improvement have not provided any advice to trusts seeking to set up subsidiary companies on their right to access private funding including patient income. The Secretary of State requires that NHS providers pay a Public Dividend Capital dividend based on a charge of 3.5% of actual average relevant net assets, including subsidiaries, during the financial year as determined in the draft/unaudited accounts submitted to NHS Improvement/the Department. The Secretary of State has the power under the Health and Medicines Act 1988, as invoked by Sch. 4 Para. 20 of the NHS Act 2006 to provide loans. However, in practice no loans have been provided to subsidiary companies of trusts.</p><p> </p><p>Local Health and Social Care Overview and Scrutiny Committees are consulted about service changes to their local NHS. No guidance has been issued to trusts who are seeking to set up subsidiary companies on submitting proposals to establish such companies to Health and Social Care Overview and Scrutiny Committees for examination.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","129620 ; 129703 ; 129704","2018-03-06T14:12:03.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850137/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850137/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850137/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-26","NHS Trusts: Subsidiary Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what guidance his Department gives to NHS trusts seeking to set up subsidiary companies on submitting proposals to establish such companies to the Health and Social Care Overview and Scrutiny Committees for examination.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","129705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850138","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-01","<p>The most recent Arts Council appointments campaign was to appoint four Area Chairs (South East Area, South West Area, Midlands Area and North Area) and additional general Council Members to its non-executive Board. Of those who applied for these roles, sixteen candidates were deemed appointable by the Advisory Assessment Panel and from these, ten appointments were subsequently made by Ministers. Six candidates deemed appointable were not appointed to the Arts Council board.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-03-01T13:33:15.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850138/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850138/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-26","Arts Council England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many candidates deemed appointable by the most recent appointment panel for the National Council of Arts Council England were not subsequently appointed.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","129706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850139","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-01","<p>Personnel deployed on Operations ORBITAL and CABRIT are in receipt of the Deployable Welfare Package, which includes Longer Separation Allowance. This means they are not eligible for a Local Overseas Allowance.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","129709","2018-03-01T15:36:26.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850139/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850139/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-26","Eastern Europe: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether personnel deployed on Operation Cabrit receive the (a) Longer Separation Allowance and (b) Local Overseas Allowance.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","129707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850140","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-01","<p>The PIP Assessment Providers are responsible for the scheduling and management of face to face assessments. While both Providers endeavour to avoid cancellations, unfortunately there will be situations where this is unavoidable, for example if an assessor is ill. When an assessment is cancelled both Providers will contact claimants as soon as possible to reschedule the assessment.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-03-01T16:07:08.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850140/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850140/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850140/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-26","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans her Department has in place to ensure that (a) people are informed when their personal independence payment assessment meeting is cancelled and (b) such meetings are re-arranged as soon as possible.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","129708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850141","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-01","<p>Personnel deployed on Operations ORBITAL and CABRIT are in receipt of the Deployable Welfare Package, which includes Longer Separation Allowance. This means they are not eligible for a Local Overseas Allowance.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","129707","2018-03-01T15:36:26.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850141/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850141/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850141/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-26","Ukraine: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether personnel deployed on Operation Orbital receive the (a) Longer Separation Allowance and (b) Local Overseas Allowance.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","129709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850142","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-01","<p>As with all operations on which we ask our personnel to deploy, the NATO Enhanced Forward Presence deployment will be kept under constant review, and a decision on whether to award a medal, or seek permission to wear any medal awarded by NATO, will be taken when it is appropriate.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-01T15:35:47.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850142/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850142/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850142/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-26","Eastern Europe: Military Decorations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to award a medal for personnel serving as part of NATO’s Enhanced Forward Presence; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","129710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850143","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-05","<p>We have made it clear that Channel 4 must have a major presence outside London. As a publicly owned broadcaster, it is essential that it reflects and provides for the country as a whole. The government is working with Channel 4 on how best it can increase its regional impact, and we will set out next steps in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","129712","2018-03-05T14:40:25.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850143/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850143/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850143/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-26","Channel Four Television: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to announce his decision on whether to relocate Channel 4.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","129711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850144","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-05","<p>We have made it clear that Channel 4 must have a major presence outside London. As a publicly owned broadcaster, it is essential that it reflects and provides for the country as a whole. The government is working with Channel 4 on how best it can increase its regional impact, and we will set out next steps in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","129711","2018-03-05T14:40:25.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850144/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850144/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850144/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-26","Channel Four Television: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what the process will be for the selection of an alternative location in the event that Channel 4 leaves its current location; and if he will he make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","129712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850145","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-06","<p>The Department has not made an assessment of the impact of child burial charges on parents in poverty.</p><p> </p><p>Funeral Expenses Payments are available to help parents, and others, on certain income-related benefits with the costs of funerals, and will pay the full fees levied for adult or children’s burials or cremations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-06T11:16:32.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850145/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850145/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850145/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-26","Burial: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the effect of child burial charges on parents living in poverty.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850146","Home Office","false","2018-03-02","<p>The arrangements for providing medical information as part of the firearms licensing process, introduced in 2016, are voluntary and we know that there is significant variation in how GPs respond to the police request for this information.</p><p>We have been in discussions with the police, the relevant medical bodies, and representatives of shooting organisations about how greater consistency can be achieved across England and Wales.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-03-02T13:30:55.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850146/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850146/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850146/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-26","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that medical practices comply with published guidance on the medical requirements for obtaining a firearms license.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","129714"
